nodes.text: A Twi'lek female singer rose to the heights of a galactic superstar during the First Order/Resistance War. She was a highly-skilled performer who commanded respect and attention from those she met. In addition to her musical career, the superstar also fought for the integrity and freedom of the Twi'lek people and operated within the criminal underworld to achieve her goals. At some point, she traveled aboard the MPO-1400 Star Cruiser Halcyon, where she encountered an aspiring Togruta musician who held her in high regard.

The galactic superstar will appear in Star Wars: Galactic Starcruiser, an upcoming hotel and entertainment experience set to open in 2022 at the Walt Disney World Resort. According to audition material posted by The Walt Disney Company for the character, the company conceptualized the singer as a Mezzo Soprano and catergorized her musical style as a "neo-soul, jazzy, funk" hybrid. The audition form suggested that applicants for the role perform the song "Abracadabra" by Judith Hill.
